 At least one person has been reported dead, and another injured during a sporadic shoot-out by Nigerian Soldiers in Apata, Ibadan, Oyo state. It is reported that the incident happened in the early hours of Saturday, 4th February 2023. Eyewitnesses told newsmen that they only saw soldiers’ vehicles pass through Brent, and all they heard were gunshots. “Everyone ran for their lives; some lay on the floor to prevent stray bullets. The eyewitness also revealed that a stray bullet hit a young man identified as Samuel, a commercial motorcyclist, who allegedly died instantly. ALSO READ: Nigerians battle to collect PVCs in Lagos Another female casualty is presently receiving treatment at Lafia Hospital in the NNPC area. It would be recalled that there were pockets of protests on some parts of Ibadan Friday owing to the unavailability of new naira notes that have led to a national outcry. 